Our club aims to support and help develop members' skills in public speaking and presentation. The primary focus of the club is to train members in the art of ceremonial presentation in the English language through various forms of activities.

Members joining the club are afforded advantages that significantly contribute to their personal growth and professional development. Primarily, all members will have the opportunity to hone their public speaking, presenting, and event moderating skills through various event-hosting activities and hands-on experiences that will further be beneficial in real-world scenarios and practical insights.

activities.imgDescription: Club members present about their chosen movie.
activities.text: In English Movie Club, our members talk, discuss, create presentations, and make reviews about all kinds of English movies. Everyone can freely express their personal ideas and views on the plot, characters, acting, and settings of the many films each group chooses to talk about on their selected day. We also explore themes, cultural aspects, and hidden messages within movies to enhance our understanding and appreciation of cinema. Furthermore, the club often hosts fun activities like trivia games about interesting vocabularies or grammars from the films. It's truly a fantastic way to improve your English skills while bonding over a shared love for movies!

benefits.imgDescription: Club members discuss about their presentation.
benefits.text:
1. Participants get to improve their social skills by brainstorming and communicating with their teammates.
  2. Participants' English speaking, listening, and writing skills are refined by conversing with our foreign teachers, listening to natural accents in films, and curating their own movie reviews.
  3. Participants can chill out in this club from the many tiring subjects this school offers.

reviews.content: This club is genuinely just pure fun and games! It's the place where I would love to hang out after a tiresome day of school. I had been in the club for 3 years straight and I must say that it didn't disappoint at all and you should definitely check it out!
